{
  "stem": "1895.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other thing that I recall very well, talking about religion again, the Gentile boys that worked with me on that kommando, who witnessed what I witnessed, you know, the arrival and the whole procedure, the gassing, and all that, they were totally convinced that this terrible misfortune that had befallen the Jews happened because of what the priest told them in the Catholic churches, that the Jews are getting it because they rejected Christ.",
      "word_count": 75
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were so convinced on that point that, you know, I myself remember as a 17-year-old, I didn't have a good argument to use against them, because it seemed at the time that was so plausible.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I mean, they were-- they were killing Poles, and they were killing Russians, and-- and their-- and their lives were almost as bad as ours.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they were not-- they were not-- there was no genocide of Poles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was no genocide of Russians.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were not sending them into the crematoria.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were not sending them into the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was reserved primarily for Jews and, in a few instances, for Gypsies.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But if you're a young man of 17 at the time-- and we talked about that many times.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They took it as a matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They took it as a gospel that the Jews are being punished for rejecting Christ.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was absolutely no question in their minds.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't start to think it was true.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My Jewishness was too inculcated in me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I remember that I-- I had no argument to use against it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't argue the point even if I wanted to, because it just seemed to make sense.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To some extent, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Up to a point, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
